Trusted signers
===============

This directory is the allowlist for SSH commit signatures. The script
concatenates every regular file here into a single OpenSSH allowed_signers
file at verification time.

One file per signer. Each file contains one or more lines:

    <committer-email> <key-type> <key-base64>

Example (file named "sven"):

    sven.seeberg@tuerantuer.org ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAA...

Example (file named "renovate-bot"):

    renovate-bot@tuerantuer.org ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAA...

Notes
-----
- The principal (the email) must match the COMMITTER email on the commits
  you want to trust. Confirm what email your Renovate bot commits with.
- Optional time windows are supported via allowed_signers options, e.g.:
    sven@... valid-before=20270101 ssh-ed25519 AAAA...
- Deploy real keys to /etc/salt-git-autoapply/trusted-signers/ (the path set
  in config.yaml). This in-repo directory is just an example/placeholder.
